
#### FREE RANGE VHDL - how to contribute ####

git (www.git-scm.com) is the version control system used to menage the 
content of this book. 
This instructions tell you how to contribute to the development
of the VHDL book "FREE RANGE VHDL".


1) get the latest latex version of the book:
    wget http://www.freerangefactory.org/dl/free_range_vhdl_tex.zip
    unzip free_range_vhdl_tex.zip
    cd free_range_vhdl_tex

2) you can see the history of the latest version of the book with:
    gitk

4) Modify and save any file you want.

5) use the file "compile" and the file "clean" to compile and to 
   clean your final book version. check the status of your work
   with the command:
    git status

5) create a patch with the command:
    git diff > my_patch.patch

6) send the file "my_patch.patch" and an explanation of what you 
    have done to:

    contact@freerangefactory.org
    




